SUMMARY:[Wk1] Ch 1 тАФ The AI Engineering Landscape + Hands-On ML
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 1/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ AI Engineering (Huyen)\nChapter: Ch 1 тАФ The AI Engineering Landscape\nFocus: Map the new AI stack: LLMs\, RAG\, agents\, evaluation\, deployment. What AI engineering is vs traditional ML.\nтЬЕ Practice: Sign up for an LLM API (OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini). Write 5-10 prompts manually. No code yet тАФ just explore model behaviour.\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 1 тАФ The ML Landscape\nFocus: Supervised vs unsupervised\, algorithm families\, challenges\, the ML workflow.\nтЬЕ Practice: Set up Python env (Colab or local). Run first notebook at github.com/ageron/handson-mlp. Get comfortable with NumPy + pandas.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 1 тАФ The AI Engineering Landscape\n    тЖТ Sign up for an LLM API (OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini). Write 5-10 prompts manual\n[ ] Ch 1 тАФ The ML Landscape\n    тЖТ Set up Python env (Colab or local). Run first notebook at github.com/ageron\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
