DTSTART:20260713T143000Z
DTEND:20260713T160000Z
SUMMARY:[Wk3] Ch 3 тАФ Evaluation Methodology + Hands-On ML
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 3/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ AI Engineering (Huyen)\nChapter: Ch 3 тАФ Evaluation Methodology\nFocus: Evaluation frameworks\, metrics\, benchmarks\, AI-as-judge pattern. Key insight: functional correctness is not enough.\nтЬЕ Practice: Design eval rubric for your Week 1 prompts тАФ what does 'good' vs 'bad' look like? Write it explicitly.\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 3 тАФ Classification\nFocus: Binary/multiclass/multilabel. MNIST project. Precision\, recall\, F1\, ROC/AUC\, confusion matrices.\nтЬЕ Practice: Build binary classifier on MNIST (digit 5 vs rest). Extend to multiclass. Observe precision-recall trade-offs.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 3 тАФ Evaluation Methodology\n    тЖТ Design eval rubric for your Week 1 prompts тАФ what does 'good' vs 'bad' look\n[ ] Ch 3 тАФ Classification\n    тЖТ Build binary classifier on MNIST (digit 5 vs rest). Extend to multiclass. O\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
