SUMMARY:[Wk6] Ch 6 тАФ RAG and Agents (most job-releva + Hands-On ML
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 6/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ AI Engineering (Huyen)\nChapter: Ch 6 тАФ RAG and Agents (most job-relevant)\nFocus: RAG architecture (chunking\, embedding\, retrieval\, reranking)\, agentic loops\, tool use. RAG = facts\, finetuning = form.\nтЬЕ Practice: тШЕ BUILD RAG PIPELINE: ingest 5-10 docs\, chunk+embed\, ChromaDB/FAISS\, query with LLM. Run eval harness on it.\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 7 тАФ Ensemble Learning + Random Forests\nFocus: Bagging\, Random Forests\, boosting (AdaBoost/GBM)\, stacking\, XGBoost. These are production workhorses.\nтЬЕ Practice: Stacking ensemble with 3 classifiers. XGBoost on housing dataset from Ch 2. Compare vs plain Scikit-Learn.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 6 тАФ RAG and Agents (most job-relevant)\n    тЖТ тШЕ BUILD RAG PIPELINE: ingest 5-10 docs\, chunk+embed\, ChromaDB/FAISS\, query \n[ ] Ch 7 тАФ Ensemble Learning + Random Forests\n    тЖТ Stacking ensemble with 3 classifiers. XGBoost on housing dataset from Ch 2.\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
