SUMMARY:[Wk13] Ch 14 тАФ Deep Computer Vision (CNNs) + DDIA 2nd Ed.
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 13/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 14 тАФ Deep Computer Vision (CNNs)\nFocus: Conv layers\, CNN architectures (ResNet/EfficientNet)\, object detection (YOLO intro)\, TorchVision.\nтЬЕ Practice: Train CNN on CIFAR-10. Load pretrained ResNet. Fine-tune it. Compare from-scratch vs fine-tuning convergence speed.\n\nЁЯУЪ DDIA 2nd Ed. (Kleppmann)\nChapter: Ch 1 тАФ Trade-offs in Data Systems Architecture (NEW)\nFocus: Every design decision is a trade-off. Cloud vs self-hosted\, distributed vs single-node\, consistency vs availability.\nтЬЕ Practice: Write 3 data system decisions from work. For each: what were you trading off? Revisit after finishing the book.\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 4/5: Weekend Deep Work\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
