DESCRIPTION:WEEK 18/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 17 тАФ Diffusion Models (most current topic)\nFocus: DDPM\, forward/reverse diffusion process\, score matching\, DDIM\, latent diffusion\, Stable Diffusion architecture.\nтЬЕ Practice: HuggingFace Diffusers: generate images. Try guided generation (conditioning on prompt). Read Stable Diffusion model card.\n\nЁЯУЪ DDIA 2nd Ed. (Kleppmann)\nChapter: Ch 6 тАФ Replication Part 1 (leaders\, lag\, failover)\nFocus: Single-leader\, multi-leader\, leaderless replication. Sync vs async. Read-your-writes\, monotonic reads\, consistent prefix reads.\nтЬЕ Practice: Draw replication topology of a DB you use. Label every arrow: sync/async? Consistency guarantee? Failure mode?\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 17 тАФ Diffusion Models (most current topic)\n    тЖТ HuggingFace Diffusers: generate images. Try guided generation (conditioning\n[ ] Ch 6 тАФ Replication Part 1 (leaders\, lag\, failover)\n    тЖТ Draw replication topology of a DB you use. Label every arrow: sync/async? C\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
