SUMMARY:[Wk20] Ch 19 тАФ Training + Deploying at Scale + DDIA 2nd Ed.
DESCRIPTION:WEEK 20/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: Ch 19 тАФ Training + Deploying at Scale\nFocus: Distributed training (data/model parallelism)\, quantisation\, distillation\, TorchScript\, TorchServe\, monitoring.\nтЬЕ Practice: Quantise a model you've trained. Measure size reduction + inference speedup. Compare accuracy before/after.\n\nЁЯУЪ DDIA 2nd Ed. (Kleppmann)\nChapter: Ch 8 тАФ Transactions Part 1 (ACID + weak isolation)\nFocus: ACID in depth. Weak isolation levels. Race conditions: dirty reads\, dirty writes\, read skew\, lost updates\, write skew\, phantom reads.\nтЬЕ Practice: For each race condition\, write concrete bug scenario in your work domain. Build personal reference card of all 4 anomalies.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 19 тАФ Training + Deploying at Scale\n    тЖТ Quantise a model you've trained. Measure size reduction + inference speedup\n[ ] Ch 8 тАФ Transactions Part 1 (ACID + weak isolation)\n    тЖТ For each race condition\, write concrete bug scenario in your work domain. B\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
