DESCRIPTION:WEEK 22/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: тШЕ Capstone Week 1 тАФ Design + Data + Baseline\nFocus: Define capstone project: fine-tuned LM for a domain\, image classifier\, tabular + neural ensemble.\nтЬЕ Practice: тШЕ CAPSTONE WK 1: Choose problem\, curate data\, run Scikit-Learn baseline. Document as GitHub portfolio project.\n\nЁЯУЪ DDIA 2nd Ed. (Kleppmann)\nChapter: Ch 9 тАФ The Trouble with Distributed Systems (revised 2nd ed)\nFocus: Partial failures\, unreliable networks\, unreliable clocks\, process pauses. Why distributed != single-node.\nтЬЕ Practice: Find a real clock-skew incident post-mortem online. Map it to this chapter's framework.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] тШЕ Capstone Week 1 тАФ Design + Data + Baseline\n    тЖТ тШЕ CAPSTONE WK 1: Choose problem\, curate data\, run Scikit-Learn baseline. Do\n[ ] Ch 9 тАФ The Trouble with Distributed Systems (revised 2nd ed)\n    тЖТ Find a real clock-skew incident post-mortem online. Map it to this chapter'\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
