DESCRIPTION:WEEK 24/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Hands-On ML (G├йron)\nChapter: тШЕ Capstone Week 3 тАФ Evaluation + Deployment\nFocus: Evaluate on held-out test set. Error analysis тАФ where does model fail? Deploy to HuggingFace Spaces or FastAPI.\nтЬЕ Practice: тШЕ CAPSTONE WK 3: Write README (problem/data/model/results/limits). Deploy. This is your interview portfolio piece.\n\nЁЯУЪ DDIA 2nd Ed. (Kleppmann)\nChapter: Ch 10 тАФ Consensus Part 2 (Raft\, Paxos\, ZooKeeper)\nFocus: Distributed transactions\, atomic commit\, fault-tolerant consensus. ZooKeeper + etcd internals. Total order broadcast.\nтЬЕ Practice: Watch raft.github.io visualisation. Sketch how etcd (used in Kubernetes) maps to what you just learned.\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] тШЕ Capstone Week 3 тАФ Evaluation + Deployment\n    тЖТ тШЕ CAPSTONE WK 3: Write README (problem/data/model/results/limits). Deploy. \n[ ] Ch 10 тАФ Consensus Part 2 (Raft\, Paxos\, ZooKeeper)\n    тЖТ Watch raft.github.io visualisation. Sketch how etcd (used in Kubernetes) ma\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
