DESCRIPTION:WEEK 32/36 тАФ AI Engineer Learning Roadmap\n================================================\n\nЁЯУЪ Patterns Dist. Systems (Joshi)\nChapter: Ch 17-20 тАФ Versioned Value\, Version Vector\, Fixed Partitions\, Key-Range Partitions\nFocus: Version numbers for history + conflict detection. One counter per node tracks causality. Stable vs sorted key range partitioning.\nтЬЕ Practice: Compare Cassandra (hash=Fixed Partitions) vs CockroachDB (range=Key-Range). What does each mean for queries + rebalancing?\n\n--- WEEKLY CHECKLIST ---\n[ ] Ch 17-20 тАФ Versioned Value\, Version Vector\, Fixed Partitions\, Key\n    тЖТ Compare Cassandra (hash=Fixed Partitions) vs CockroachDB (range=Key-Range).\n\nтП▒я╕П Session 1/5: Deep Read + Theory\nЁЯУЕ 10-12 hrs/week ┬╖ Huyen ┬╖ G├йron ┬╖ DDIA 2nd Ed ┬╖ Joshi
